# 1. プロを目指して

Saki: Alright! We're gonna have another great practice today♪
Saki: Let's head to SEKAI already!
Shiho: Saki, keep it down. Everybody can hear you.
Shiho: And like I told you a second ago, there's still too many people around today so we'll have to wait a little more until we do head over.
Ichika: Ever since we played that show, she's been as worked up as ever.
Honami: We may've just been the opening act, but we finally got a chance to perform together. The crowd seemed really into it towards the end too...
Saki: I know, it was sooo much fun! I wanna do a show like that again!
Honami: Hehe. But don't push yourself too hard, okay?
Saki: Of course, I'll be extra careful! But we're still gonna practice lots and lots♪
Saki: We all decided to try and go pro, together. Since then, I've been having a lot more fun trying stuff out on my synthesizer instead of going out somewhere!
Ichika: Really? I never thought I'd hear you say anything like that, Saki...
Shiho: I know, right? Honestly, I thought she'd be the one asking for more time off for us to go out together.
Saki: What?! No, I wouldn't!
Saki: I mean, whenever I start feeling tired, my mind might wander towards doing something else...
Saki: But wanting to get better and go pro with all of you always comes out on top! I've just never been this enthusiastic before!
Honami: Hehe. And we'd expect nothing less from you, Saki.
Shiho: In that case, why don't we raise the bar a little for what we do during warm-ups?
Saki: What?! You're gonna make things harder than before?!
Shiho: Is that a complaint? You said you want to get better as fast as possible, right?
Saki: Y-Yeah, but...
Shiho: Don't worry, Saki. I'll just be adjusting what we do based on the level you've risen to...
Saki: Risen...? You're saying that I've actually gotten better? Yay! I love you so much, Shiho!
Shiho: S-Saki... L-Let go... I can't move...
Saki: No! I'm really happy because you praised me, Shiho♪
Shiho: *Sigh*... Okay...
Honami: Oh, I almost forgot...!
Honami: Didn't you say during lunch that you'd like to talk to us about practice today, Shiho?
Shiho: Yeah, I did.
Ichika: Is there something you'd like to discuss?
Shiho: Sort of... I guess now's a good time since we still can't head over yet...
Saki: Tell us! Tell us!
Shiho: It's about what we'll be doing specifically moving forward as Leo/need.
Ichika: What we'll be doing...?
Saki: Oh, I get it! It's like our first meeting to plan Operation Go Pro As Leo/need, right♪
Honami: When did you come up with that name, Saki?
Saki: Just now! So about what we'll be doing...?
Shiho: Right... This might take a while, so let's find an empty classroom where we can talk.
Shiho: I'd like to start with what we'll need to do if we really are going to try and go pro.
Shiho: First, there are a few ways to become professional musicians...
Saki: Oh, I know! By auditioning and stuff, right?
Saki: Like those shows where the winners get a big record deal♪
Shiho: Right, auditioning is one path that's open to us.
Shiho: Performing at live houses, getting better over time, and growing our fanbase is another option.
Honami: I see. An agency might scout us out after we've gained enough popularity.
Shiho: Exactly. But it'll specifically be a record company instead of an agency.
Ichika: Audition or earn fame through live house performances...
Shiho: Those are just the most standard routes, but there are other ways of going about this too.
Shiho: Lately, some artists have been finding the spotlight by making videos and posting them online.
Saki: That's cool... You know so much, Shiho!
Shiho: Well, regardless of which path we choose, we're still nowhere near playing like actual pros yet.
Shiho: That's why we need to prioritize practicing, honing our skills, and getting experienced as much as we can.
Honami: Getting experience... Does that mean we should perform in more shows too?
Shiho: Yes, it does.
Shiho: I'm sure you all felt it during our last performance, but it doesn't matter how well you do during practice. Everything can still fall apart while we're on stage.
Shiho: For the very first time, we had a crowd of people hear our music and saw how they reacted to our performance...
Ichika: You're right. I couldn't sing at all at first because I was so scared. It was just such a big venue with so many people there...
Ichika: But I was so desperate to tell you how I felt that before I knew it, I was able to find my voice.
Saki: Me too! After I started focusing on wanting you to stay, Shiho, I was able to settle down and play normally!
Honami: Right. It felt like we all found the courage to rise up to the occasion.
Shiho: Oh...
Shiho: I was trying to say that we should perform while focusing on how our audience reacts, but... Thanks.
Shiho: I'm sure as we keep playing more and more shows, we'll keep on improving too.
Shiho: Not just technically either. We'll get more used to playing in front of a crowd.
Ichika: Right... I'd like for us to get better and see more people coming to our performances.
Honami: I'd like that too...!
Saki: It's kinda scary, but really fun at the same time... If it means getting better, then I wanna do that too.
Shiho: Okay. Then we can start focusing on performing in more shows.
Saki: More shows...! This is so exciting!
Honami: Hehe. I can't wait either.
Honami: But how do we actually go about doing that? We've never even chosen where to perform before.
Shiho: Don't worry about that.
Shiho: I asked the owner of the live house I work at and got the green light to perform in some events.
Saki: Whoa! You're awesome, Shiho♪ Thank you so much!
Shiho: We have about a month to prepare for it, and I understand that it's going to be tight. Would you guys still be up for it...?
Ichika: A month... I'm okay with that. What should we play?
Honami: How about the song we played when we opened for STANDOUT? I feel like we'll be able to play it much better now.
Shiho: Yeah, I thought about that too. But they're going to give us about 15 minutes to play, so we'll probably need two more songs to fill out our slot.
Saki: Wait, three songs?!
Honami: That means we have to make a decision on our other two songs soon.
Shiho: We do... Let's try going through the songs we've been practicing, some we might want to try and pick a couple out of that.
Ichika: Okay. There are a few Miku songs that I've been wanting to try, so I'll make sure to look them up.
Ichika: But... It'd be nice to compose our own song and play it during a show too.
Saki: Our own song...?
Shiho: But we'll have to start making our own songs too if we're gonna actually go pro. Just keep that in mind.
Saki: Yeah, I remember Shiho mentioning that we're gonna have to start making our own songs!
Saki: It'd be awesome if we could!
Honami: I agree. Performing the songs you personally made must be so much fun.
Saki: Right?! Ichi and I tried giving music to some lyrics we came up with... But if we're gonna actually play it during a show, I want to make something better!
Shiho: Maybe someday.
Ichika: You're okay with just someday?
Shiho: Putting together a song that we can play on stage is no simple task.
Shiho: We'd have to figure out how we're going to do that too.
Saki: But we have you, Shiho, so we'll be fine, right? You've been playing for bands forever too...
Shiho: No way. Arranging music a little is the most I can do.
Saki: What?! I didn't know that!
Shiho: A long time ago, I tried making some songs myself, but it ended up being too much...
Shiho: I just wasn't able to turn what I was imagining into music.
Honami: I see... If you had that much trouble, Shiho, then it must be incredibly difficult.
Shiho: But I do want to make songs with you guys since we've decided to go pro together.
Shiho: And we can try our hand at it little by little as we practice.
Saki: While we practice...? Oh, in that case...
Shiho: ...?
Saki: What if we each tried coming up with riffs and phrases starting next practice?
Shiho: Our own riffs...? Like short melodies or chord progressions?
Saki: Yeah! Coming up with a whole song at once is too hard, but I know we can at least come up with snippets of one!
Honami: That does sound interesting... But can we get that to work?
Ichika: We've never done anything like that before, but...
Ichika: I'd like to give it a try.
Saki: Yeah, let's do it! Who knows? We might end up making something really good♪
Shiho: Okay... Starting small sounds like a good idea.
Shiho: We can do that starting tomorrow.
Saki: Yay! Let's give it our best shot!
Ichika: Hehe. Saki's just jumping for joy.
Honami: Oh, since there are fewer people around now, shall we head over to see Miku and the others?
Shiho: Right, and I still want to talk about us as a band.
Saki: Okay! Let's go go go♪
Saki: (Our own shows, our own songs... Hehe. This is sooo much fun!)
Saki: (I'm gonna give it everything I've got!)
